AC  GenProp0973
DE  Enterobacterial common antigen (ECA)
TP  METAPATH
AU  Haft DH
TH  0
CC  The enterobacterial common antigen is composed of a repeating
CC  trisaccharide unit (Fuc4NAc-ManNAcA-GlcNAc).  Fuc4NAC is
CC  4-acetamido-4,6-dideoxy-D-galactose and ManNAcA is
CC  N-acetyl-D-mannosaminuronic acid.  Polymerization and translocation
CC  from the cytoplasmic face to the periplasmic face of the plasma
CC  membrane is handled by an ECA-specific wzx/wzy/wzz system.
**  Evidence for step 13 is also used for GP0912, GP0932, GP0947, GP0953 and GP0968.
